import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.countplot(x="source", data=data, color='blue', ax=ax)
    ax2 = ax.twinx()
    sns.countplot(x="target", data=data, color='red', ax=ax2)
    ax.set_xlabel('Source')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of source and target in the dataset?')
    ax.legend(title='Source', loc='upper left')
    ax2.legend(title='Target', loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['source', 'target']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    pivot = data.pivot('source', 'target', 'count')
    sns.heatmap(pivot, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues')
    plt.title('What is the most common source and target combination in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('source').agg({'target': 'mean'}).reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='source', y='target', data=data)
    ax.axhline(y=data['target'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
